ng-class-odd.
    - used to apply the css classes to the odd rows of table.


ng-class-even.
    - used to apply the css classes to the even rows of table.


Syntax.

.even{
    color:red;
}

.odd{
    color:green;
}

<table>
    <tr ng-repeat="x in data" ng-class-odd="'odd'" ng-class-even="'even'">
        //Logic Goes Here
    </tr>
</table>



ng-switch.
    - used to write switch cases in angular applications.


Syntax.

   <div ng-switch="expression">
        <div ng-switch-when="value1">
                //Logic
        </div>

        <div ng-switch-when="value2">
                //Logic
        </div>

            --
            --

        <div ng-switch-default>
                //Logic
        </div>
 </div>


 ng-cloak.

     - used to avoid the blinking / flickering of the web page before display the output.

















